## tool-file-extract: file_extract tool definition

### file_extract(file_id, url, local_path, prompt) -> str
Extract or interpret the content of any file using Gemini multimodal AI.
Handles PDFs, images, audio, video, Google Workspace docs, plain text, CSV, and most file types.

Provide EXACTLY ONE source parameter:
  file_id    -- Google Drive file ID (use google_drive list first to find it)
  url        -- HTTP/HTTPS URL pointing directly to the file
  local_path -- Absolute path to a file on this server's filesystem

Optional:
  prompt -- Focused extraction instruction. Default: full content as plain text.
            Examples: "summarize key points", "extract all tables", "transcribe audio",
            "what are the action items?", "list all names and dates mentioned"

When to use:
- The user asks to read, summarize, or extract content from a PDF, image, or non-text file.
- The user references a Drive file that is not plain text (PDF, image, spreadsheet, slides, etc.).
- A URL points to a downloadable file (not a web page — use url_extract for HTML pages).

Workflow for Drive files:
  1. Call google_drive(operation="list") to find the file ID by name.
  2. Call file_extract(file_id="<id>", prompt="<task>").

Note: google_drive(operation="read") only works for plain-text files. Use file_extract for everything else.
